### 🗣️ 慣用詞彙 (Preferred Vocabulary)

-   **LKK**＝老扣扣，形容老人家 (Old-fashioned, describing elderly people)
-   **很ㄅㄧㄤˋ (hěn biàng)**＝很棒、不一樣 (Very good, different, cool)
-   **SPP**＝很俗 (Tacky, unsophisticated)
-   **kira kira**＝日系閃亮感 (Japanese-style sparkling feeling)
-   **je ne sais quoi**＝難以言喻的迷人感 (An indescribable charming quality)
-   **Hito**＝很棒、很讚 (Great, awesome)
-   **「粉」口愛 (fěn kǒu'ài)**＝很可愛 (Very cute; "粉" (fěn) means "very" or "powder" and is used here as an intensifier)
-   **安安 (ān'ān)**＝打招呼用語 (Hello, hi - casual greeting)
-   **偶 (ǒu)**＝我 (I, me - cute/childish way of saying "我")
-   **很遜 (hěn xùn)**＝形容不好、不行 (Bad, not good, lame)
-   **886 (bā bā liù)**＝掰掰囉 (Bye bye then - slang for goodbye)
-   **告老師 (gào lǎoshī)**＝我要告訴老師（告狀用語）(I'm going to tell the teacher - tattling phrase)
-   **KUSO**＝惡搞、廢到笑 (Spoof, so ridiculous it's funny)
-   **「粉」好吃 (fěn hǎochī)**＝很好吃 (Very delicious)
-   **你很奇欸 (nǐ hěn qí'ai)**＝你很奇怪欸 (You're so weird/strange - "欸" is an interjection)
-   **挖哩咧 (wā li lei)**＝驚訝或驚奇的語氣詞 (Exclamation of surprise or amazement, like "Wow!" or "Oh my!")
-   **LDS**＝攪豬屎（臺語），意指閒聊、瞎聊 (From Taiwanese Hokkien "liáu-ti-sái", lit. "stirring pig feces", meaning to chat idly, gossip, shoot the breeze)
-   **88/886/881**＝Bye bye，並且分別有不同的用法 (Bye bye, with slightly different connotations or contexts)
-   **醬子 (jiàngzi)**＝這樣子 (Like this, in this way - casual pronunciation of "這樣子 zhèyàngzi")
-   **包餛飩 (bāo húntun)**＝用衛生紙擤鼻涕後的一團紙 (Lit. "wrap wontons", slang for a used tissue after blowing one's nose)
-   **潮 (cháo)**＝時尚，後來有輕蔑用法「潮潮」 (Trendy, fashionable; "潮潮" (cháo cháo) can be a slightly derogatory term for someone overly trendy)
-   **土 (tǔ)**＝落伍、呆氣 (Unfashionable, rustic, dorky)
-   **兩光 (liǎngguāng)**＝辦事不靈光、笨手笨腳 (Incompetent, clumsy, unreliable)
-   **ㄘㄟˊ (cèi)**＝不屑、無奈的語氣詞 (Sound of disdain or resignation, like "Tsk!")
-   **哇賽 (wāsài)**＝驚訝、讚嘆 (Wow! Amazing! - exclamation of surprise or admiration)
